blurb: A compact rogue-like dungeon crawl board game through a realm of metal and madness packed in a cassette tape case!
creator/biography:
Cassette Games is a new founded small publisher specialised in creating games that fit in an old school Cassette Tape Case. The ultimate metal/punk/rock vibe games with blood, gore, dark humour and on top of that interesting and good gameplay!
We are a team of experienced designers, artists and developers and we have many games under our belt (big ones and smaller ones) but to be honest we haven't been excited about something as much as this in a long time!

rewards/1/description:
This is for brick and mortar retailers only. We love our FLGS! This is a deposit and we'll collect the remainder as we get closer to fulfillment.

To qualify as a retail backer you need to have a physical location and a tax id number.
If you have multiple locations we need each location to back the game separately if you want them shipped to each location.

You will receive an itemized invoice prior to final delivery.
The invoice will list each item on your order, broken down by price, as well as the shipping fee, and the application of your KS pledge as a deposit. The invoice will need to be paid in full before your order is shipped.

During the Late Pledge, we will reach out to each retailer through the email associated with your Kickstarter account to confirm order quantities.

blurb: Unleash the battle of farting grannies, cane brawls, and garden-based burglary in this family-friendly team based board game!
creator/biography: Once upon a time, two little boys in plaid shirts met in kindergarten. They both grew up and each of them married their own babe with big blue eyes. They stayed best friends. Their blue-eyed babes became best friends, too. They all played games together...like lots and lots...and lots of games together. After more than a decade of games, (whew that went fast) they were inspired to make their own game company together, Fry Sauce Games. And if you know anything about fry sauce...you should know...

add_ons/3/description: This limited 17-card set lets players maximize their 2-player dream experience by infiltrating and manipulating the dream of their opponent. This set includes 10 silver and black holofoil cards (Dark Dreamer Set), and 7 glow-light dream cards (Technicolor Dreamer Set). When you play with these cards, you'll never dream the same again.

add_ons/4/description: Your doom is inevitable as gigantic and ancient thing wakes from the deepest pits of the Earth. The cataclysmic event stirs other unnamable and forgotten creatures. Humankind will soon be no more. \n\nThis fast-paced card and dice game pits player against player (2-player game) as they fight to be the last to survive the horror of the last day of man. Each player controls a deck of monsters which are manipulated to attack the other deck. One at a time, the creatures dwindle in number as they players avoid the bloodlust, a most furious feeding frenzy. Everyone dies, but the first player to run out of monsters loses the game. A lot of luck and as much strategic thinking is required to outlive your opponent. Certain die rolls will unlock certain abilities and options.

rewards/3/description:
Get a copy of the game AND

You can become a student in the game! Each student has a name, and your name would be prominently written on the teacher board, the student boards, and on the Note cards.

What To Do: Submit your name while following the requirements below, and we'll put it onto one of the desks in the game.

Requirements: 
Must be your actual name or nickname of yourself or someone you know
The desks are arranged alphabetically based on the first letter of your name, so there is only one slot for each letter.

Once a letter is claimed it will be updated on here.
The associated student picture is not guaranteed to look like you. Scroll down to "Become a Star Student" to unlock a picture of yourself as a student.

blurb: A Mensa-like strategy board game app where players pit their wits against each other to complete a "FuzeLine circuit for the win
creator/biography: Hey there! I'm Zou, kid at heart and founder of DBI Studios. In all seriousness, I'm undertaking the creation of unique, mind-challenging and competitive apps. They are...different, to say the least. The genesis of my latest project (and my first on KickStarter), FuzeLine, occurred in 2005 when I was working as an engineer in Princeton, NJ. I’m inspired by both complexity and simplicity, and when they meet, magic happens.Rezky_A

name: FuzeLine
rewards/1/description:
You will have the opportunity to test the game through first access to development versions of FuzeLine. Your feedback will be invaluable to making this the best competitive 1 v 1 and tournament and strategy game in the app stores, available for both Apple and Google devices.

You will be able to offer your feedback through the app and know that every comment we receive will be taken seriously. 

We are working hard to test on all devices, from sign up, to friend requests, rematches, game invites and more.
